            {/* Key Insights */}
            <div className="mt-6 p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg">
              <h4 className="font-semibold text-indigo-900 mb-2">Key Circadian Insights</h4>
              <div className="text-sm text-indigo-700">
                <p><strong>Peak AEA Window (7-9 PM):</strong> Optimal time for intimacy, meditation, and cannabis therapy. This natural peak enhances CB1 receptor sensitivity and emotional connection.</p>
                <p><strong>Cortisol-AEA Inverse Relationship:</strong> As cortisol decreases throughout the day, AEA naturally increases. Stress reduction techniques can amplify this effect.</p>
                <p><strong>2-AG Midday Peak:</strong> Highest levels during afternoon support energy, focus, and social engagement. Ideal time for physical activity and social interactions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Genomic & Microbiome Integration */}
          <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
